<HEADLINE> VISA Opens Emergency Service Center in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- VISA International, the world's
leading credit card company, opened China's first VISA Product
Replacement center today in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The center, located at the Shanghai Branch of the Chinese Bank
of Industry and Commerce, will provide wide-ranging services for
credit cardholders, including access to cash withdrawals and
emergency application for new cards.
</P>
<P>
VISA introduced the service to China in response to the
nation's flourishing tourist industry and credit card companies
which are attracting ever more foreign cardholders, said Zhang
Kaichun, a VISA senior manager.
</P>
<P>
VISA has established 30 similar centers around the world,
including 20 in Asia-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, China's commercial and financial center, has more
than 1,000 ATM machines linked to the global VISA/PLUS
Network. The network also enables cardholders access to
withdrawals in yuan, the Chinese currency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
