<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qinshan Nuclear Power Station Undertakes Satisfactory Overhauling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Qinshan Nuclear Power
Station, the first facility of its kind which opened in China in
1991, temporarily suspended operations on July 14 this year for
its fourth upgrade and refueling project
</P>
<P>
The Qinshan Nuclear Power Company, which operates the station
in east China's Zhejiang Province, said the examination and
cleaning of key equipment has been completed satisfactorily.
</P>
<P>
The station has operated for 73 months since going online, with
previous upgrade projects carried out in 1994, 1995 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
The plant has operated safely, with no adverse impact on the
surrounding environment, according to a company spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He added that the company has hired a number of experienced
professional to proceed with the upgrading to discover and fix
possible problems.
</P>
<P>
The station, which operates under the principles of "Safety
First" and full responsibility, will reenter operations only after
receiving approval from the National Nuclear Safety
Administration, according to the spokesman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
