<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Doubles Specialists Eliminated in Shanghai Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- "The Woods", Australian
doubles world No.1 pairs, stopped their paces in the singles of
the Shanghai Open ATP Tour Friday when they lost in the
quarterfinal matches.
</P>
<P>
Eighth-seeded Todd Woodbridge was defeated by American Michael
Chang, second seed, 6-2, 6-2, while his doubles partner Mark
Woodforde lost to Dutch fifth-seeded Paul Haarhuis 7-6, 7-6.
</P>
<P>
Woodbridge almost had no answer to Chang's overwhelming
strikes, and was broken five times before lossing in straight
sets.
</P>
<P>
Woodforde showed lack of consistence as he surrendered twice
at tie-breakers, one at 9-7 and the other at 7-4.
</P>
<P>
It is the third Australian fall on Friday after Michael
Tebbutt lost to Ramon Delgado of Paraguay 6-4, 6-7, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Croatian top-seeded Goran Ivanisevic booked the last berth of
the semifinals as he overpowered Kenneth Carlsen of Denmark 6-2,
7-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
