<HEADLINE> Preparations for National Trade Union Congress Set for Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Preparations have been completed
for the 13th National Congress of Chinese Trade Unions, which will
be held in Beijing between October 19-25, the All-China Federation
of Trade Unions announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Vice-chairperson Ni Haomei said the congress will host some
2,000 delegates from wide-ranging sectors, including the railway,
civil aviation, finance and posts and telecommunications
industries, as well as representatives from 31 provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Ni noted that a major task of the congress will be to establish
Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guiding ideology for trade union work in
China.
</P>
<P>
Over 80 percent of the delegates will reportedly have at least
two year advanced education, up 15.4 percent on the previous, with
nearly 40 percent holding senior professional titles, up 8.5
percent on the 12th congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
