<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SETC Official Discusses Business Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- China will focus greater
attention on the development of small and medium-sized enterprises
in order to help ensure stable economic growth, according to the
State Economic and Trade Commission (SETC).
</P>
<P>
The SETC has established a special department in charge of the
macro management and coordination of related enterprises,
according to SETC deputy secretary-general Meng Xiangang.
</P>
<P>
Meng is attending the second Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation
(APEC) Fair for small and medium-sized enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Reelated enterprises play a major role in the Chinese economy
by contributing 60 percent of the nation's gross domestic product
and 40 percent of tax revenues. They also employ some 75 percent of
the workforce, according to Meng.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China, the nation's central bank, and all
Chinese commercial banks are currently drafting policies and plans
to help related enterprises raise funds, said Meng, adding that
the the government will also provide certain levels of
technological and personnel support.
</P>
<P>
Economists have warned that blind expansion of the sector will
lower economic efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The one-week event in Yantai, a port city in east China's
Shandong Province, is jointly sponsored by the APEC and SETC.
</P>
</TEXT>
