<HEADLINE> Chinese Leaders Visit Photo Exhibition of Late Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 9 (Xinhua) -- High-ranking Chinese officials
visited a photo exhibition today at the Beijing Library to mark
the 100th birth anniversary of late Chinese President Liu Shaoqi.
</P>
<P>
Among the visitors were Wei Jianxing, member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and member of the secretariat of
the CPC Central Committee, and Vice-Premier Li Lanqing, a member
of the same standing committee.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition featured 300 photographs, a number of personal
items, and various publications and video documents recording the
life of this great proletarian revolutionary, statesman, and
outstanding leader of the Communist Party of China and the
People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Liu Shaoqi was born in Ningxiang County in Hunan Province on
November 24, 1898. He rose to the position of president in the
late 1950s and early 1960s and was widely recognized as a "public
servant who served the people" and contributed to China's
revolution and construction.
</P>
<P>
Other Chinese leaders Li Tieying, Zeng Qinghong, Zou Jiahua, Ren
Jianxin, Wan Guoquan, Jing Shuping, Luo Haocai and Wang Wenyuan
also visited the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
The photo exhibition will be presented in a number of provinces
and cities over the next two months, including Shaanxi, Sichuan,
Henan and Guangdong provinces, and the cities of Tianjin and
Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is sponsored by the Ministry of Culture, and the
CPC Central Committee's Party School, the Party Literature
Research Center and Party History Research Center, as well as the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
