<HEADLINE> S. Korea Leads in Asian Youth Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- South Korea led the 9th Asian
youth volleyball championship on Friday after beating Australia
15-13, 15-13 and 15-9, collecting four points.
</P>
<P>
This is the South Koreans' second win in group A of the
tournament. On Thursday, they defeat Qatar 15-9, 15-2, 15-3 .
</P>
<P>
In other group A match Friday, Japan beat Sri Lanka 15-9,
15-7, 15-8 after a defeat from Iran on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In group B competition, Pakistan, who was beaten by China on
Thursday, edged the UAE 15-9, 15-13, 14-15 and 15-8.
</P>
<P>
China will match Kazakstan while India will meet the Chinese
Taipei Friday night. The group also includes Pakistan, India and
the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
The eight-day 9th Asian youth volleyball championship kicked
off in Tehran on Thursday with a participation of 12 teams.
</P>
</TEXT>
