<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 16:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat Condemns New Killing, as Violence Goes on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National Authority
(PNA) Chairman Yasser Arafat has condemned the killing of an
Israeli woman soldier Friday by a Palestinian man, Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio quoted Netanyahu as saying that Arafat, who is on
a visit to Russia, condemned the stabbing in a telephone
conversation with him.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu said earlier that the incident underlines Israeli
demands that the PNA uproot terrorism infrastructure on its
territory. Labor Party leader Ehud Barak also said that terrorism
must be fought relentlessly.
</P>
<P>
These remarks came after the Israeli woman soldier was stabbed
to death at about 11 a.m. (0900 GMT) in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Radio reports said the 19-year-old victim was attacked soon
after she got off a bus at an intersection to the Jewish
settlement of Tomer, about 10 kilometers north of the
Palestinian-ruled town of Jericho. She was a resident of the
settlement.
</P>
<P>
Two other Tomer residents who witnessed the stabbing chased
after the assailant, who run towards a nearby Palestinian
village, shooting and wounding him in the legs, the radio
said. The 34-year-old man was interrogated while being treated in
an Israeli hospital.
</P>
<P>
Jewish settler leaders urged Israeli army to enter the
Palestinian village where the assailant lives to punish his
family, saying that Israel should not give up lands to the
Palestinians and expect them to fight terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 10 Palestinians and a Spanish journalist were
injured in the West Bank town of Hebron as hundreds of
Palestinians clashed with Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The clashes erupted before a funeral for a Palestinian who was
killed by Israeli soldiers in a clash Thursday. The mourners, who
chanted slogans and carried banners denouncing Jewish settlers,
threw rocks and firebombs at Israeli soldiers. The soldiers
responded with rubber bullets.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli car mistakenly entering a Palestinian town near
Hebron was stoned and two children inside were slightly injured,
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Hebron has been one of the flashpoints between Israel and the
Palestinians since it was divided under an agreement signed early
last year. Violence broke out almost daily since a dozen Israeli
soldiers were injured by a grenade attack on September 30 and
Israel imposed a curfew on the Israeli-controlled part.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the stabbing Friday would cast a shadow on the
coming Washington summit next week between Netanyahu, Arafat and
U.S. President Bill Clinton, during which an agreement is
expected to be reached on the second Israeli withdrawal from the
West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Tensions have been high in the West Bank since Israel sealed
off the areas and the Gaza Strip last month following the killing
of two members of the Islamic militant group Hamas by Israeli
troops.
</P>
<P>
Hamas has repeated its threat to attack Israelis in
retaliation, including committing suicide bombings and kidnaping
hitchhiking Israeli soldiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
