<DOCNO> XIE19981010.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-09 17:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8 Killed by Floods, Landslide in Northern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Floods and landslide caused by
torrential rain have killed eight people in Iran's northern
province of Gilan, an provincial official announced on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jamshid Rasaee, director general of the Natural Catastrophe
Department of Gilan said people in rural areas of Rudsar and
Khorge Gil Asalem in the province suffered heavy damages in the
floods Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The people have been caught in the flood waters of the
cloudburst, he said, quoted by the official news agency IRNA, all
road links to the rural areas of Rudsar, Rezvan Shahr, Masaleh
have been cut off due to flood waters.
</P>
<P>
He said over four hundred rural families were stranded and
his department has asked Tehran for two whirlybirds to come to
the aid of people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
