<HEADLINE> Russia Supports Palestine in Building Independent State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Russia supports Palestinians and
their leadership in efforts to create an independent state,
Russian Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting here Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat,
Ivanov said that this is "stategic goal" for Russia to back the
Palestinian desire.
</P>
<P>
The creation of an independent Palestinian state "cannot
contradict Israel's national interests, especially in the sphere
of security," Ivanov, who had just returned from London, was
quoted by the Foreign Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
He described as "rational and justified" the Palestinian
leadership's line toward reaching a compromise on the unsettled
aspects of the PLO agreements with Israel and at implementing the
commitments made by the sides in full.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, at the meeting, reiterated his leadership's intention
to strictly follow the letter and spirit of the agreements
concluded with Israel and use every opportunity to work out new
mutually acceptable accords.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Palestinian leader called on Russian diplomats
to energetically assist in efforts toward guiding the course of a
settlement in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Arafat completed his two-day official visit to
Moscow with satisfaction.
</P>
<P>
During the visit he met with Russian President Boris Yeltsin,
Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov, vice-Prime Minister Valentina
Matviyenko and State Duma speaker Gennady Seleznyov.
</P>
<P>
He also met with representatives from the Yabloko, Our Home is
Russia and Communist Party of Russian Federation factions in the
lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
During the visit the Palestinian and Russian sides signed an
agreement on trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has left Moscow for Helsinki. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
