Turkish President Suleyman Demirel to arrange a visit to Ankara by
Moussa in the coming few days within the framework of Egypt's
mediation efforts.
</P>
<P>
"Syria rejects threats and is keen on finding diplomatic
solutions to all pending problems between the two countries,
especially security ones," al-Sharaa told reporters after the
meeting with Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Asked on reports claiming that Syria is backing some Turkish
terrorist organizations especially the outlawed Kurdish Workers'
Party (PKK), al-Sharaa said he did not want to go into details as
Egypt is following the Syrian view and conveying it to the Turkish
side.
</P>
