<HEADLINE> Azerbaijani President Strives for Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijani President Heydar
Aliyev, in a bid to win the coming presidential election, said on
Saturday that he alone "can lead Azerbaijan along the road of
development and progress", the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a radio broadcast, Aliyev, 75, said that no presidential
candidate had so many years leadership experience as he had.
</P>
<P>
He also said other candidates were lying in their campaign
speeches when they promised sharp improvements in living standards.
</P>
<P>
"I have tried to do as much as possible to improve the lives
of our people. I believe that the people will voice their
confidence in me on October 11 and I will continue my work," he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Azerbaijani presidential poll is scheduled for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Presidential candidates include: chairman of the Social
Well-being Party Khangusein Kyazimli, chairman of one of the three
Azerbaijani Communist parties Firudin Gasanov, president of the
Political Repression Victims' Association Ashraf Mekhtiyev,
chairman of the National Independence party Etibar Mamedov, and
Independent Azerbaijan Party leader Nizami Suleymanov. 
</P>
