<HEADLINE> Spleen Recipient on Recovery Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Wu Lianjie, 28, the first spleen
transplant patient in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, has
survived one month following the complicated surgery.
</P>
<P>
Doctors at the No. 1 Hospital under the Harbin Medical University
performed the surgery.
</P>
<P>
Wu suffers from hemophilia, the only known cure for which is a
spleen replacement. Wu's father, 49, donated the replacement organ.
</P>
<P>
Wu's recovery is progressing and he has regained the ability to
walk.  
</P>
</TEXT>
