<HEADLINE> Armed Forces Abandon Business Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army
(PLA) and the Armed Police Force must strictly adhere to a recent
decision the central authorities announced concerning dissociating
from business activities, according to senor military leader Yu
Yongbo.
</P>
<P>
Yu, member of the Central Military Commission and director of
the PLA General Political Department, made the remark during a
recent Beijing work conference centered on preparations to either
transfer, dissolve or otherwise restructure enterprises currently
operated by military and armed police units.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), the State Council and the Central Military Commission
convened a meeting and reached the decision on disallowing the
armed forces from involvement in business activities.
</P>
<P>
Related units must systematically study the series of Deng
Xiaoping's expositions on battling corruption, said Yu, adding the
studies must also focus on related major speeches made by
President Jiang Zemin, also chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the army and armed police force must provide
full support for the CPC Central Committee and urged the units to
concentrate on implementing the decision.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ke, a member of Central Military Commission and director
of PLA General Logistics Department, emphasized that the PLA army
must fulfill its historic tasks under the correct leadership of
the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core. 
</P>
</TEXT>
