<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 393 Drug Cases Reported in Kuwait This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Three Hundred and
ninety-three drug-related cases were referred to court in Kuwait
in the first seven months this year, the Kuwait News Agency
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Waleed Al-Majil, head of Kuwait's Drugs and Alcohol Department,
was quoted by the news agency as saying that 85 cases were related
to drug trafficking and the rest to narcotics addiction.
</P>
<P>
Most of the persons involved are Kuwaiti nationals, Al-Majil
said, adding that the drug addicts are mostly young people.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the rampant drug problems in his country to
frequent travels to overseas by Kuwaitis and massive influx of
laborers from more than 100 countries.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf sheikdom witnessed 662 drug cases last year, of which
131 were related to drug smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Alarming rise in drug trafficking and narcotics abuse have
become challenging problems for the government and the society in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that 4,456 persons were arrested from 1991 to
1997 in Kuwait due to involvement in drug-related cases.
</P>
<P>
Official figures have showed that 1,068 drug dealers have been
arrested till the end of last May, most of whom were involved in
crimes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
