<HEADLINE> France Opens Consulate General in Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 10 (xinhua) -- France opened a consulate general
in this capital of central China's Hubei Province today, its third
in China following those in Shanghai and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
This is also the first consulate ever established in Wuhan
since 1949 when the People's Republic of China was founded. The
move follows an agreement reached between the Chinese and French
governments this April.
</P>
<P>
According to Consul General Francois Sastourne, the consulate
is the first set up by France this year, and it deals with
consular affairs in three provinces: Hubei, Hunan and Jiangxi.
</P>
<P>
French Ambassador to China Pierre Morel said at the opening
ceremony that France is the largest source of Hubei's foreign
investment, and the present move shows France's confidence in
cooperating with China.
</P>
<P>
Hubei Provincial Governor Jiang Zhuping said on the same
occasion that the consulate general will help expand France's
cooperation with Hubei and the central part of China as well.
</P>
</TEXT>
