<HEADLINE> Germany Pushes for Creation of EU Sports Counci </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany has pushed for the
creation of a special European Union council of sports ministers
and suggested to hold a European tribunal for sports in 1999,
local press reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new and old problems within the realm of sports led
Germany to its suggestion for the creation of the sports council
and the inauguration of the sports tribunal, according to the
European Report, a journal that specializes in European Union
affairs.
</P>
<P>
The European competition commissioner is now faced with a
total of 56 cases involving sports, the latest complaint coming
this week from the Media Partners aiming at the Union of European
Football Associations (UEFA).
</P>
<P>
Several cases have already been open including doping in sports
, especially in the Italian football and this year's Tour de
France cycling race.
</P>
<P>
A consensus was being built toward EU's formation of a common
policy regarding sports in the materialization of the appeal now
incorporated into the European community's Amsterdam Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The clause appeals emphasizing the social significance of
sport, in particular its role in forging identity and bringing
people together.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission has been called to listen to sports
associations when important issues affecting sport are at stake.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
