<HEADLINE> Serbia to Tighten Domestic Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's Republic of
Serbia has decided to bring economic and press activities under
tight control if it is confronted with NATO military action.
</P>
<P>
A government decree to take effect Saturday stipulated that
corporations and private enterprises should continue their
operations in case of NATO attacks.
</P>
<P>
They should also ensure a timely and sufficient supply of daily
necessities and refrain from hoarding and cornering. Otherwise,
their commodities will be confiscated and business suspended, said
the decree.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, mass media are forbidden to carry articles or
broadcast programs that are against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The media should not disseminate negative reports that might
cause panic among the people or weaken their determination to
maintain the country's territorial integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
