<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-10 10:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait's Ministries, Departments to be Sued for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Kuwaiti Environment
Protection Authority (EPA) has planned to sue 11 state ministries
and government departments for polluting local environment.
</P>
<P>
According to the English-language daily Arab Times, cases will
be lodged against the Ministries of Public Works, Electricity and
Water, Health and Interior.
</P>
<P>
Other government authorities such as Kuwait Municipality,
Public Authorities for Housing Care, Kuwait University, Kuwait
Oil Company, and even the National Assembly will also be sued for
their environmental neglectfulness.
</P>
<P>
The EPA said the Ministry of Public Works has mismanaged its
drainage department. Some of its facilities are emitting nauseous
odors that have affected many people throughout the country, it
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the EPA, the Ministry of Electricity and Water
uses a sulfur-rich fuel which is believed to be hazardous to
residents, especially to children.
</P>
<P>
While Kuwait University was accused of failing to keep its
faculty campus tidy, Kuwait Municipality was singled out for
dumping large quantity of dangerous waste in the vicinity of
certain residential areas.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait Oil Company is said to have poured the equivalent of
thousands of barrels of oil in holes in a practice that is
environmentally unsound.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti Environment Protection Authority is monitoring the
local environment closely at a day-to-day base.
</P>
<P>
An environment offender in Kuwait is usually convicted to be
responsible for cleaning the polluted areas or get fined, or
both. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
