<HEADLINE> Bangkok Police Make Biggest Amphetamine Drug Haul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangkok metropolitan police
stumbled onto the biggest amphetamine drug haul in the capital
city of Thailand Friday night, seizing almost 1.6 million tablets
valued at 127.6 million baht (3.27 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
A police source said Saturday that anti-drug squads, acting on
a tip-off, discovered the drugs in a hotel room in central
Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Seven people, including four women, were arrested. They
admitted that they intended to sell the drugs on the street.
</P>
<P>
Thai Interior Minister Sanan Kachornaprasart led an
investigation into the case and was interrogating the suspects,
the source said on condition of anonymity. 
</P>
