industrialized city of Osaka for home on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Before leaving Osaka, the last leg of his four-day visit to
Japan, Kim said to more than 700 Korean residents in the city that
his state visit to Japan was "a great success." (South Korea-Japan)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro will have a busy
agenda trying to resolve the current government crisis in the wake
of Prime Minister Romano Prodi's resignation on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Prodi lost the vote of confidence in the Lower House of
parliament by 313 votes to 312. He then handed in his
resignation, which had already been accepted by President
Scalfaro.(President-Government Crisis)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
DHAKA -- At least five persons were killed and 45 others
injured in a road accident in Bangladesh on Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in northern district of Gazipur when a
Dhaka-bound passenger bus collided head-on with a truck coming
from opposite direction. (Bangladesh-Accident)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic said here
Friday that the situation in Kosovo is improving and the war-like
atmosphere will soon fade and politics will take over.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic made the remarks during a meeting with US envoy
Richard Holbrooke on restoring peace to Kosovo. It was the fourth
time they met for talks since Monday. (Yugoslavia-Milosevic-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SOFIA -- Bulgaria will be cautious about joining any possible
military action in Kosovo, said Prime Minister Ivan Kostov here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody has wanted Bulgaria to join an armed intervention in
Kosovo yet," Kostov said in parliament in response to a statement
of the Democratic Left pressing the government for a categorical
"no" to any request for intervention in the turbulent Yugoslav
province of Kosovo.(Bulgaria-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
MADRID -- The Spanish government announced Friday that Spain
will participate in possible air strikes against Yugoslavia over
the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, a government spokesman,
however, said NATO's use of military force against Yugoslavia can
be realized only when all political and diplomatic efforts have
failed. (Spain-NATO-Air Strikes)
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A volunteer for Humanity activist working with
rape victims of the May riots was found dead at her Central
Jakarta house on Friday evening, the Jakarta Post reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The victim, identified as Martadinata and popularly known as
Ita, 18, was found with her neck slashed and stab wounds on her
hands, abdomen and chest.  (Indonesia-Killing) 
</P>
