<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 142,500 Chinese Take Exams for Lawyer Qualification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- China started the Tenth National
Lawyer Qualification Examinations simultaneously across the
country today.
</P>
<P>
A record of 142,500 applicants have registered for the test
this year, 28,000 more than in 1997. The two-day exam is held in
310 sites across the country.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Justice Gao Changli said in Beijing that since the
exam first introduced in 1986, 900,000 candidates have taken the
exam, and 110,000 of them passed and obtained qualification for
becoming a lawyer.
</P>
<P>
Passing the test is a must for obtaining qualification as a
lawyer in China today.
</P>
<P>
"Practice in the past 12 years has shown that as the system of
rule by law is being enforced in China and the role of lawyers
brought into play in political and economic life, the profession
of lawyer has been paid more attention to and is what many young
people aspire to go in for," Gao said.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the sharp increase of applicants in this
year's test lies in the restructuring and streamlining of
government bodies, an official with the Justice Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
"Many government employees are thinking about going into the
profession of lawyer once they are fired," he said.
</P>
<P>
Now, lawyers account for 0.008 percent of the Chinese
population and cannot meet the needs of social and economic
development, therefore the needs for qualified lawyers is very
large, Justice Minister Gao said.
</P>
<P>
According to a government plan, China expects to have 150,000
lawyers by the end of 2000.
</P>
<P>
Gao also said that the government is also concerned about the
quality and proficiency level of lawyers. His ministry is going to
do more to improve the examination system by learning useful
practices from other countries to ensure both the academic level
and equity, fairness of examinations.
</P>
<P>
"Our aim is to promote high-quality talents to meet increasing
needs," Gao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
