<HEADLINE> 36 Die of Diarrhea, Gastroenteritis in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, October 10 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of diarrhea and
gastroenteritis since last month has claimed at least 36 lives in
Saptari district, eastern Nepal, press reports here said.
</P>
<P>
At least 16 people have died of diarrhea, which broke out last
month due to polluted water and fish and adulterated cooking oil,
The Kathmandu Post reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
And 20 others have succumbed to gastroenteritis which broke out
a few days ago in some parts of the district, the official RSS
news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Local hospital has treated about 1,500 gastroenteritis patients
and 16 were still undergoing treatment, it added.
</P>
<P>
At least five others had died of gastroenteritis since
September 29 in Jhapa district, eastern Nepal, RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, encephalitis is hitting some parts of the country as
well, claiming dozens of lives, reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
