<HEADLINE> 9 Killed, 45 Injured in Road Mishap in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- At least five persons were killed
and 45 others injured in a road accident in Bangladesh on Friday
evening, press reports said Saturday, quoting police and hospital
sources.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred in northern district of Gazipur when a
Dhaka-bound passenger bus collided head-on with a truck coming
from opposite direction, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Both the vehicles fell into roadside ditch after the collision
leaving five passengers in the bus dead on the spot.
</P>
<P>
Of the injured, 15 critically-injured persons were shifted to
different hospitals of Dhaka and others were treated locally.
</P>
<P>
Police seized the vehicles but the drivers of the bus and the
truck managed to escape.
</P>
<P>
The case in this connection has been registered and is under
investigation. 
