<HEADLINE> Forest Parks to Be a Pillar Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Forest parks will become a
pillar industry of the forest sector when the number of such parks
jump to about 2,000 by the year 2010 from the present 874, China
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
By then, the parks -- covering 19 million hectares -- will
greatly contribute to people's environmental awareness while
protecting forests, wild animals and plants, the daily quoted an
official of the State Forestry Bureau as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the daily, 292 of the existing forest parks have
become national parks authorized by the former Forestry Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Between 1992 and 1997, forest parks across the country received
300 million visitors and brought two billion yuan (241 million US
dollars) of direct income.
</P>
<P>
During the past decades, these parks contributed over one
billion yuan (120 million US dollars) to modernizing scenic spots
and building hotels and shops to cater to visitors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
