<HEADLINE> More Foreign Tourists Arrive in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5.043 million
foreign tourists arrived in Thailand in the first eight months
this year, an increase of 5.59 percent compared with the same
period last year, according to the Tourism Authority of Thailand
(TAT)
</P>
<P>
Thailand is one of the few countries in Asia to report growth
in Tourist arrivals this year.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's two strongest visitor markets are Europe, with
arrivals up by 22.26 percent to 1.37 million, and North America,
with a 14.24-percent increase to 343,211.
</P>
<P>
Arrivals from East Asia have dropped by 4.06 percent to 2.79
million.
</P>
<P>
In August alone, tourist arrivals rose by 7.19 percent with
European arrivals soaring by 29.39 percent over the same month
last year.
</P>
<P>
Tourists from the West have been attracted this year by the
prospect of low cost vacations in Thailand, and have been
traveling less to neighboring countries where political and social
unrest is a concern, the TAT was quoted Saturday by the Bangkok
Post as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
