<HEADLINE> Drought Expected in Central Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Central Thailand will face such
an acute drought next year that some farmers will be asked to
plant less paddy and city people will be told to cut down on water
consumption, the Irrigation Department warned.
</P>
<P>
The coming drought will be more drastic than the last one, the
department's chief Pramote Maiklad was quoted Saturday by the
Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The combined volume of water in bhumibhol and Sirikit dams, the
two major reservoirs supplying water for the central Thailand, is
4 billion cubic meters compared to last year's 8.4 billion cubic
meters at the same period.
</P>
<P>
Water for households and agricultural use will be 50 percent
less. Bangkok residents will be asked to save water and tap water
pressure will drop, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
