Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party is considering
setting aside a total of 67 trillion yen (about 577.6 billion
dollars) in public funds to fix the country's ailing banking
sector.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- The Pension Council, an advisory body to Japan's Health and
Welfare Ministry, has drawn up a report on a pension reform plan
that proposes future cuts in pension payments and increases in
contributions.
</P>
<P>
Yomiuri:
</P>
<P>
-- Tokyo prosecutors eye filing criminal charges against former
executives of the ailing Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan on
suspicion of breach of trust.
</P>
<P>
Nihon Keizai
</P>
<P>
-- An advisory panel to Japanese Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi is
considering tax deduction on housing loan interest. 
</P>
