<HEADLINE> IMF President to Visit Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- International Monetary Fund
(IMF) President Michel Camdessus will visit Honduras next month, a
senior Honduran official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Honduran government is negotiating a program to make
financial adjustments with the IMF and is hopeful of a final
agreement before the visit by Camdessus, said Honduran Finance
Minister Gabriela Nunez.
</P>
<P>
The program, euphemistically called the "expanded structural
adjustment facility," would permit Honduras to obtain fresh
resources and would serve as a guarantee for the Central American
country to renegotiate its 1.2-billion-U.S.-dollar debt with the
Paris Club of creditors, an affiliate of the IMF.
</P>
<P>
The IMF president is expected to arrive in Honduras on November
18. He will also participate in an anti-corruption forum here.
</P>
</TEXT>
