<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Nicaragua, Causes No Damage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.9
degree on the Richter Scale jolted western Nicaragua off the
Pacific coast Friday morning, but no damage or death were reported
so far, said government sources.
</P>
<P>
Sources from a Nicaraguan institute on territorial studies said
the quake occurred at 5:54 local time. The epicenter was located
11.87 degrees north latitude and 86.77 degrees west longitude, 98
miles southwest of Managua, the capital city of Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Strong tremors were felt in nearby cities of Managua, Masaya,
Leon, Granada and Rivas. But till Friday afternoon, there were no
reports of damage or death caused by the earthquake.
</P>
<P>
Local seismologists said the quake was an event related to the
movement of the Cocos and Caribbean tectonic plates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
