<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hearts Vow to Challenge UEFA Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Scottish club Hearts vowed on
Friday that they will continue their fight to remain in the Cup
Winners' Cup, despite UEFA turning down their appeal.
</P>
<P>
The Scottish Cup holders are furious that their appeal against
Real Mallorca over non-regulation goalposts was dismissed on
Thursday by UEFA's disciplinary committee on a technicality.
</P>
<P>
Hearts were told that their appeal had failed because they did
not register it in writing before the kick-off of the first-round
second leg match in Palma on October 1.
</P>
<P>
But Hearts chief executive Chris Robinson said on BBC Radio on
Friday: "This story has some way to run. Our appeal was dismissed
on a technicality but we are hopeful that now UEFA have the
evidence in front of their eyes, they might change their mind."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
