<HEADLINE> Ghana Backs New Nigerian Govt: Rawlings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian President Jerry
Rawlings said Friday that Ghana would continue to support the
Nigerian government in its efforts to establish democratic rule
in Nigeria, Ghana News Agency (GNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
"This support is based on principles," he said when General
Abdulsalam Abubakar, the Nigerian Head of State, called on him at
the Castle, Osu, at the start of a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Rawlings said Nigeria had faced international condemnation
because the international community did not understand its
complex situation.
</P>
<P>
He referred to the volatile situation during the regime of
late General Sani Abacha and congratulated Abubakar on his
efforts at reducing the tension.
</P>
<P>
"You have demonstrated outstanding leadership and it is our
hope that the international community will continue to support
you to give Nigeria a breathing space to sow the seed of a stable
Nigeria," Rawlings said.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Abubakar said in reply that "Ghana has been an
outstanding friend of Nigeria" and thanked President Rawlings for
defending Nigeria at various fora during its most difficult
times.
</P>
<P>
Ghana has given him a lot of support since his assumption of
office following the death of General Abacha in July this year,
Abubakar said. 
</P>
