<HEADLINE> Bahrain Crown Prince Meets U.S. Defense Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Crown Prince of Bahrain Sheikh
Hamad Bin Isa al-Khalifa met here Friday with visiting U.S.
Defense Secretary William Cohen to exchange views on the situation
in Middle East and related issues.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Manama, the crown prince, who is also
commander-in-chief of Bahrain's armed forces, also discussed with
Cohen ways of strengthening defense cooperation between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Bahrain, the central Gulf island state has provided facilities
for U.S. Navy warships for decades, and its role was important to
the U.S. Navy operations during the 1990 Gulf Crisis.
</P>
<P>
Cohen arrived in Manama Thursday night to start a tour of the
members states of the Gulf Cooperation Council, which groups
Bahrain, Oman, Kuwait, Qatar, Saudia Arabia and the United Arab
Emirates.
</P>
<P>
He was to listen to comments and evaluation by Gulf leaders on
the situation in Iran and their proposals on America's role in the
regional affairs, reports said.
</P>
<P>
It was also reported that the Gulf states have expressed their
intention to purchase U.S. missile systems to cope with the
situation in the Gulf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
